{
  "stem": "7157.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I brought-- I always liked to catch things, like whether it was worms or butterflies or what have you.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I brought a little jar with me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And, and I found there was a little pond, there, where the little guppies were-- all kinds of little fish, little guppies, maybe half-inch size or something like that.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I started collecting these little guppies in my jar.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I collected them, like for all day, collected fish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was a lot of fun.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And finally we, we decided we were ready to go home, it was getting dark.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I'm walking home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I stumbled on something, and the jar fell.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And all the fish spilled out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I yelled out, [POLISH], which, translated means 'the fish got spilled.' And I guess the reason it's such a funny story because, even today, when Mindy or Ellen-- my kids-- or my wife drop something, I say [POLISH], meaning that they dropped something.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's [POLISH], you know?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That one word still catch-- stays with us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The fish got spilled, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we basically, you know, went, went through this time frame, you know, escaping, hiding.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I remember being in a house where when my-- sometimes Wujek would go with my mother, at least part of the way, to help her buy or sell the cigarettes or do something, or find food.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he would leave us alone in this one room.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And most of those times, you know, the bathrooms weren't part of the house.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The bathroom was maybe 100 yards away, an outhouse.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were asked to-- when they left, they said, you can't go to the bathroom.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You're not allowed to go the bathroom, because you'll be seen, and George will be seen.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
